<TITLE> PMO staffer Habib gets 3 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 11 (bdnews24.com)  A special court dealing with graft suspects Monday sentenced prime minister's office staffer SM Ahsan Habib to three years for extortion. The same court sentenced Bengal Consultant owner Mirza Khabir, charged in the same case, to two years' rigorous imprisonment. Judge Md Firoz Alam of Special Judges' Court-1 also fined Habib Tk 95 lakh or three more months in jail on failure to pay the fine. Both Habib and Khabir are presently fugitive. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case against the two with Tejgaon Police Station on April 2 last year. According to case details the two accused demanded a bribe of Tk 1 crore from businessman Chowdhury Afzal in exchange for releasing a huge cache of cigarettes held by customs officials. The businessman paid a total of Tk 93.50 lakh, the case alleges. The court indicted Habib and Khabir on Oct 28 last year. bdnew
